description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A Nightmare Super-Transformation!! Freeze's Battle Power of One Million.

Japanese: Akumu no Chōhenshin!! Sentōryoku Hyakuman no Furīza (悪夢の超変身!!戦闘力100万のフリーザ)

Frieza reveals a dark secret from Vegeta’s past, but the villain has an even more shocking secret in store for the Z-fighters! As the monster’s power level rises to terrifying new heights, all hope for the universe seems lost!
name: Fighting Power: One Million??

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Is This the End!? A Brutally Transcendent Power Attacks Gohan.

Japanese: Koko made ka!? Kyōaku Chōzetsu Pawā ga Gohan o Osō (ここまでか!?凶悪超絶パワーが悟飯を襲う)

Frieza claims his first victim, Krillin, and Gohan must summon every ounce of his strength in order to save his friend. Can the young Saiyan put a stop to Freiza’s ruthless onslaught, or is he destined to become the next victim?
name: Gohan Attacks

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Tide Suddenly Turned!! Piccolo, the Warrior Who Came Late.

Japanese: Ikki ni Keisei Gyakuten!! Okurete Kita Senshi - Pikkoro (一気に形勢逆転!!遅れてきた戦士・ピッコロ)

Gohan and Krillin continue their struggle against the overwhelming powers of Frieza, but as the fighting reaches its peak, a new warrior arrives on the battlefield to aid them in their efforts!
name: Piccolo the Super-Namek

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Piccolo's Self-Confidence! I Will Be the One to Defeat Freeza.

Japanese: Pikkoro no Jishin! Furīza o Taosu no wa Ore da (ピッコロの自信！フリーザを倒すのはオレだ)

Piccolo quickly takes control of the battle with Frieza, and the putrid purple monster is shocked to learn the secret behind his opponent’s powers!
name: Déjá Vu

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Attack, Goku!! An Enraged Freeza's Second Transformation.

Japanese: Shutsugeki da Gokū!! Gekido no Furīza ga Daini no Henshin (出撃だ悟空!!激怒のフリーザが第2の変身)

Just as it appears that Piccolo has gained the upper hand, Frieza quickly dashes all hopes for victory by revealing his second monstrous transformation!
name: Frieza's Second Transformation

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Fear Me!! Freeza Does Battle with a Third Transformation.

Japanese: Kyōfu Shiro!! Furīza wa Sando no Henshin de Shōbu Suru (恐怖しろ!!フリーザは3度の変身で勝負する)

Unable to watch as Piccolo is overwhelmed by Frieza, Gohan springs into action! Meanwhile, Vegeta devises a risky plan for transforming himself into a Super Saiyan!
name: Another Transformation?

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Death of Dende... Come Forth! Intense, Wide-Open Power.

Japanese: Dende no Shi... Dete Koi! Tobikiri Zenkai Pawā (デンデの死…でてこい！とびきり全開パワー)

Having reached his ultimate form, Frieza is determined to destroy the remaining Z-fighters one by one, but Vegeta boldly announces the end of Frieza’s tyrannical reign! Are Vegeta’s claims true? Has he become a Super Saiyan?
name: Dende's Demise

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: How I've Waited for this Moment!!! Son Goku Revived.

Japanese: Machi ni Matta ze, Kono Shunkan!!! Son Gokū ga Fukkatsu da (待ちに待ったぜ、この瞬間!!!孫悟空が復活だ)

Despite his new powers, Vegeta proves no match for Frieza! Meanwhile, Goku’s time in the rejuvenation chamber is nearly complete! Can he reach the battlefield in time to save his friends?
name: The Renewed Goku

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Such Regret...!! Vegeta, Pride of the Saiyans, Dies.

Japanese: Munen...!! Hokori Takaki Saiyajin Bejīta Shisu (無念…!!誇り高きサイヤ人・ベジータ死す)

Goku rejoins his friends on the battlefield, but not before Vegeta is defeated by Frieza! As the Saiyan Prince clings to life by a thread, he reveals the secrets of his violent past.
name: The End of Vegeta

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Curtain Rises over the Ultimate Battle!! I Am Going to Defeat You!

Japanese: Chō Kessen no Makuake da!! Omēdake wa Ora ga Taosu (超決戦の幕開けだ!!おめえだけはオラが倒す)

Feeling a new sense of connection to the dwindling Saiyan race, Goku wages war on the monstrous Frieza! As the fight intensifies, Frieza directs his energy blasts at Namek itself, turning the planet into a lava-spewing war zone!
name: The Ultimate Battle

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Two Superpowers Collide! A Fistfight Where Both Turn Serious!!!

Japanese: Gekitotsu no Ni Dai Chō Pawā! Honki Dōshi no Nikudan Sen!!! (激突の2大超パワー！本気同士の肉弾戦!!!)

Goku and Frieza continue their epic battle! An underwater attack puts Goku on top until Frieza traps him in an energy ball! It's fun and games for Frieza, but the exploding ball may prove deadly for Goku!
name: Clash of the Super Powers

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Freeza's Terrible Declaration! I Will Defeat You Without Using My Hands.

Japanese: Furīza Kyōfu no Sengen! Te o Tsukawazu Omae o Taosu (フリーザ恐怖の宣言！手を使わずお前を倒す)

Frieza vows to beat Goku without using his hands, but the mighty Saiyan soon makes the mosnter eat his words! Elsewhere, Captain Ginyu uses his Body Switch Technique on Bulma, leaving her trapped in the body of a frog!
name: Frieza's Boast

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: That Was No Idle Boast!! Son Goku, an Audacious, Wonderful Guy.

Japanese: Hattari ja nē zo!! Daitan Suteki na Yatsu - Son Gokū (ハッタリじゃねえぞ!!大胆素敵な奴・孫悟空)

Captain Ginyu returns to the battlefield in Bulma's body! Can Piccolo, Krillin, and Gohan handle this Femme Fatale? Later, Frieza powers up to fifty percent of his maximum, and Goku finds himself completely outmatched!
name: Bold and Fearless

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Showdown!! The Embodiment of Flame in a 20-Times Kaio-ken Kamehame-Ha.

Japanese: Ketchaku da!! Honō no Keshin Nijūbai Kaiōken no Kamehameha (決着だ!!炎の化身20倍界王拳のカメハメ波)

Goku’s powerful Kaio-Ken attack has no effect on Frieza, who is still only fighting with fifty-percent of his power! Just as it seems Frieza has won the battle, a dream-like vision helps Goku ascend to a higher level of power and strength!
name: Embodiment of Fire

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A Super-Huge Genki Dama — I'm Playing My Last Card!!

Japanese: Chō Tokudai no Genki Dama Kore ga Saikyō no Kirifuda da!! (超特大の元気玉これが最後の切り札だ!!)

Once again, Goku is rescued by a vision! This time, Vegeta talks to Goku from beyond the grave to offer new hope and encouragement! But when Goku realizes that the battle against Frieza is futile, he turns to his last resort: the Spirit Bomb!
name: Trump Card

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Keep the Chance Alive!! Piccolo's Suicide Support Strike.

Japanese: Chansu o Ikase!! Pikkoro Sutemi no Engo Shageki (チャンスを生かせ!!ピッコロ捨身の援護射撃)

Yamcha, Tien, and Chiaotzu find themselves in serious trouble when the Ginyu Force invades King Kai’s planet! Meanwhile, as Frieza thwarts Goku’s efforts to gather energy for the Spirit Bomb, Piccolo must enter the battle!
name: Keep the Chance Alive

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Incredible Destructive Force of the Genki Dama!! Who Will Survive?!

Japanese: Genki Dama no Chō Hakairyoku!! Ikinokotta no wa Dare da!? (元気玉の超破壊力!!生き残ったのは誰だ!?)

Chaos erupts on King Kai’s planet as the Z-fighters battle the Ginyu Force! Back on Planet Namek, the life and death struggle between Piccolo and Frieza rages on, and Goku completes his Spirit Bomb!
name: Power of the Spirit

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Transformed At Last!! Son Goku, the Legendary Super Saiyan.

Japanese: Tsui ni Henshin!! Densetsu no Sūpā Saiyajin Son Gokū (ついに変身!!伝説の超サイヤ人・孫悟空)

A victory celebration comes to a halt when Frieza reappears! With no reserves left, Goku watches helplessly as Frieza directs his fury at Piccolo and Krillin. Enraged by the loss of his friends, Goku undergoes a wild transformation!
name: Transformed at Last

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: An Explosion of Anger!! Goku, Avenge Everyone's Deaths.

Japanese: Ikari Bakuhatsu!! Gokū yo, Minna no Kataki o Uttekure (怒り爆発!!悟空よ、みんなの仇を討ってくれ

Engulfed in golden light, Goku announces that he is now a Super Saiyan! Frieza is unimpressed - until the fighting begins! In a raging battle, Frieza is horrified when he realizes that Goku is now superior to him in every way!
name: Explosion of Anger

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Destruction of Planet Namek!? A Demonic Flash Pierces the Ground.

Japanese: Namekkusei Shōmetsu ka!? Daichi o Tsuranuku Ma no Senkō (ナメック星消滅か!?大地を貫く魔の閃光)

Finding himself no match for Goku, Frieza attacks Planet Namek! Unable to react in time, Goku is forced to watch helplessly as the fiery blast rips through Namek’s core! Can anyone survive such incredible destruction?
name: Namek's Destruction

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: I Will Be the One Who Wins... Risking Survival, a Final Attack.

Japanese: Katsu no wa Ore Da... Ikinokori o Kaketa Saishū Kōgeki (勝つのはオレだ…生き残りをかけた最終攻撃)

With only minutes to go before the planet explodes, Frieza reaches his maximum power! Meanwhile, Gohan and Bulma race back to Goku’s spaceship. Can Goku defeat Frieza in time to rejoin his son and fly to safety?
name: A Final Attack

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Shen Long, Run Yourself Through Space!! The Time of Namek's Destruction Draws Near.

Japanese: Shen Long yo Uchū o Hashire!! Semaru Namekkusei Shōmetsu no Toki (神龍よ宇宙を走れ!!迫るナメック星消滅の時)

The battle between Goku and Frieza rages on! Back on Earth, the seven Dragon Balls have been restored, but with Namek’s destruction imminent, can Kami and Mr. Popo summon the Eternal Dragon before it’s too late?
name: Approaching Destruction

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: I Am Son Goku's Son!! Gohan Returns to the Battlefield.

Japanese: Boku wa Son Gokū no Musuko da!! Gohan, Futatabi Kessenjō e (ボクは孫悟空の息子だ!!悟飯、再び決戦場へ)

Frieza’s victims have been wished back to life, but as they begin to rise, Goku falls - overwhelmed by Frieza’s devastating assault. Sensing his father’s defeat, Gohan rushes to the scene as the universe’s final hope.
name: Gohan Returns

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: I'm Staying on This Planet!! A Final Wish Towards Victory.

Japanese: Ore wa Kono Hoshi ni Nokoru!! Shōri e no Saigo no Negai (オレはこの星に残る!!勝利への最後の願い)

Guru and the people of Namek have been brought back to life, and the dragon Porunga has reappeared to grant the last of three wishes. While a newly enraged Goku resumes his onslaught against the evil Frieza, Dende races to make the final wish!
name: The Last Wish

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Let's Get It On!! Two Remain on a Vanishing Planet.

Japanese: Tokoton Yarōze!! Kieyuku Hoshi ni Nokotta Futari (ととことんやろうぜ!!消えゆく星に残った二人)

Goku chooses to stay behind and finish his fight with Frieza. With Namek set to explode any second, there seems no way for Goku to defeat Frieza and escape in time! Has the Super Saiyan made the greatest mistake of his life?
name: Dual on a Vanishing Planet

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Pathos of Freeza! Once He Starts Shaking, He's Unstoppable!!

Japanese: Aware Furīza! Furue Dashitara Tomaranai!! (哀れフリーザ！震えだしたら止まらない!!)

Time grows short for Goku as each passing second brings Namek closer to ultimate destruction. As the Super Saiyan’s strength increases with every blow, it appears his epic battle with Frieza has at last reached its conclusion!
name: Pathos of Frieza

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Goku's Declaration of Victory!! As Freeza Destroys Himself..

Japanese: Gokū no Shōri Sengen da!! Furīza ga Jimetsu suru Toki... (悟空の勝利宣言だ!!フリーザが自滅する時…)

Frieza lashes out in a blind rage, launching a reckless volley of energy attacks. In the face of Goku’s superior power, the evil tyrant’s greatest fear has finally been realized: defeat at the hands of a Super Saiyan!
name: Frieza Defeated!!

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Freeza Defeated!! A Single Blast Packed with a Totality of Rage.

Japanese: Furīza Yabureru!! Subete no Ikari o Kometa Ichigeki (フリーザ敗れる!!すべての怒りをこめた一撃)

Even after being sliced into pieces by his own energy disk, Frieza isn’t ready to release his stranglehold on the universe. With what little power he has left, Frieza fires a final energy blast after Goku as he leaves the battlefield!
name: Mighty Blast of Rage

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Planet Namek's Great Explosion!! Goku Disappears into Space.

Japanese: Namekkusei Dai Bakuhatsu!! Uchū ni Kieta Gokū (ナメック星大爆発!!宇宙に消えた悟空)

Even though it looks like Goku is trapped on the exploding planet Namek, Dende has a good reason to celebrate: the Dragon Balls have the power to bring Goku back! But if that’s the case, why does everyone still look so sad?
name: Namek's Explosion... Goku's End?

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Son Goku Survived — The Z Warriors All Resurrected!!

Japanese: Ikiteita Son Gokū Zetto Senshi ga Zen'in Fukkatsu da!! (生きていた孫悟空Ｚ戦士が全員復活だ!!)

It is a time of joyful reunions as old friends long absent are finally wished home with the Dragon Balls! Krillin and Yamcha are brought back from the spirit world, but Porunga, the Namekian dragon, has startling news about Goku!
name: Goku's Alive

description: THE RETURN OF DEATHSTROKE AND TOMMY MERLYN -- Malcolm (John Barrowman) puts Oliver (Stephen Amell) and Thea (Willa Holland) in a dangerous situation that lands them on Lian Yu with Oliver's former enemy, Deathstroke (guest star Manu Bennett). A flashback reveals when Oliver and Maseo (guest star Karl Yune) returned to Starling City to retrieve the Omega bio weapon, and despite being under strict orders from Amanda Waller (guest star Cynthia Addai-Robinson) not to reveal himself to anyone, Oliver looks in on his family, Laurel (Katie Cassidy) and Tommy (guest star Colin Donnell).
name: The Return

description: When Cyborg and Starfire find a baby bird, it awakens their inner child.
name: Hose Water

description: Mordecai and Rigby want to win a happy birthday song contest.
name: Happy Birthday Song Contest

description: Homer is put in charge of keeping Princess Kemi out of trouble while her father, a Nigerian king, works out a uranium deal with Mr. Burns. When Kemi ends up at Moe's, Moe jumps to the conclusion that she must be related to the Nigerian prince who scammed him over email, and schemes to get his money back. But much to his surprise, he finds himself falling for the princess.
name: The Princess Guide

description: While Gordon seeks information about the recent controversy with Commissioner Loeb, Fish's allegiance with the prisoners is questioned when she appears to join forces with Dr. Dulmacher (guest-star Colm Feore). Meanwhile, after an attack close to home, Bruce deals with the aftermath.
name: Everyone Has A Cobblepot

deck: Aaron claims he can be trusted, but Rick isn't easily won over.
name: The Distance

description: After Young Justice easily takes out the HIVE while the other Titans make silly jokes, Robin decides the team needs to get serious.
name: Let's Get Serious

description: Malcolm (John Barrowman) is captured by Ra's al Ghul (guest-star Matt Nable) and taken to Nanda Parbat. Because of his love for Thea (Willa Holland), Oliver (Stephen Amell) considers saving Merlyn. Ray (Brandon Routh) is obsessed with finishing his Atom suit so he can save the city, but Felicity (Emily Bett Rickards) fears he is heading down the same path as Oliver (Stephen Amell) and tries to pull him out of the lab.
name: Nanda Parbat

description: Jake's son TV discovers a lost diary and sets out to solve a decades-old mystery.
name: The Diary

description: Benson wants to feel better about himself.
name: Benson's Suit

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Dispute Over Love! Minako and Makoto Face Off.

Japanese: Koi no ronsō! Minako to Makoto ga tairitsu (恋の論争!美奈子とまことが対立)

Minako and Makoto clash over their opposing views on love. Wanting to break the tension, Usagi takes the girls to check out a new accessory shop, unaware that Petz and Calaveras run the place.
name: A Charmed Life

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Parental Love? A Curry Triangle Relationship.

Japanese: Usagi no oyagokoro!? Karē na sankaku kankei (うさぎの親心?カレーな三角関係)

Chibi-Usa's class is having a parent-child curry party this weekend. After hearing that neither Kenji nor Ikuko can attend due to prior commitments, Usagi decides to go in their place.
name: A Curried Favor

description:
Japanese title: Umi yo Shima yo Bakansu yo! Senshi no kyūsoku (海よ島よバカンスよ!戦士の休息)

The girls enjoy some vacation time on an island. But during lunch Chibi-Usa and Rei get into a small fight, causing an angry Chibi-Usa to go out to the sea alone.
name: The Beach, the Island and a Vacation: The Guardian’s Break

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Protect Chibiusa! Clash of the 10 Warriors.

Japanese: Chibiusa wo mamore! Jū senshi no daigekisen (ちびうさを守れ!10戦士の大激戦)

Chibi-Usa leaves the house after being scolded by Usagi. Roaming the streets alone, Chibi-Usa is overcome with sadness and begins to cry, which draws the attention of Rubeus and the Four Spectre Sisters.
name: Naughty 'N' Nice

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Awaken, Sleeping Beauty! Mamoru's Distress.

Japanese: Mezame yo nemureru bishōjo! Mamoru no kunō (目覚めよ眠れる美少女!衛の苦悩)

Mamoru has a dream in which a mysterious voice warns him that being with Usagi will bring her great misfortune. Meanwhile, Sailor Moon is put into a deep coma after being attacked by a Droid.
name: Prediction of Doom

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A Battle of the Flames of Love! Mars vs. Koan.

Japanese: Ai no honō no taiketsu! Māzu tai Kōan (愛の炎の対決!マーズVSコーアン)

Wiseman predicts that Chibi-Usa will appear at Hikawa Shrine. Learning of this, Rubeus orders Koan to go down there and eliminate their target.
name: Enemies No More

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: For Friendship! Ami and Berthier Clash.

Japanese: Yūjō no tame! Ami to Beruche gekitotsu (友情のため!亜美とベルチェ激突)

Ami enters the World Chess Tournament, which is being held at the newly constructed Chess Tower. But Bertheir is also there, forcing Ami to transform and reveal her identity as a Sailor Guardian to the enemy.
name: Checkmate

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Rubeus the Heartless: The Tragic Sisters.

Japanese: Hijō no Rubeusu! Kanashimi no yon shimai (非情のルベウス!悲しみの四姉妹)

Having run out of patience over the Spectre Sisters' continual failures, Rubeus gives Petz and Calaveras one last chance to eliminate Rabbit and the Sailor Guardians once and for all.
name: Sibling Rivalry

description: The group has a difficult time molding to a new lifestyle, forcing them to consider whether they can be the people they once were.
name: Remember

description: Chief Wiggum is mistakenly delivered a military jet pack, which he gleefully accepts and uses in order to fight crime. But when the jet pack crashes into the church, the congregation, led by Marge, must resort to gambling and counting cards in order to collect money to repair the church.
name: Sky Police

description: The Titans visit Starfire's homeworld, Tamaran.
name: Tamaranian Vacation
A Formidable, Unknown Warrior! Here Comes Lucy!
The Fated Reunion - Bellamy the Hyena
Rivalry of Warriors! B Block on Fire!

description:
Original English and Japanese titles:

English: A UFO Appears! The Sailor Warriors are Abducted.

Japanese: Yūfō shutsugen! Sarawareta Sērā Senshi-tachi (UFO出現!さらわれたセーラー戦士たち)

Chibi-Usa finally learns that Usagi is Sailor Moon. Eager to return to the future, she steals Usagi's Silver Crystal and flees, only to be ambushed by Rubeus.
name: Rubeus Evens the Score

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Defeat Rubeus! The Battle in Space.

Japanese: Rubeusu wo taose! Uchūkūkan no kessen (ルベウスを倒せ!宇宙空間の決戦)

Rubeus succeeds in taking four of the five Sailor Guardians prisoner. He then demands that Sailor Moon bring Chibi-Usa and the Silver Crystal to him in exchange for the girls' lives.
name: Rubeus Strikes Out

description:
Original English and Japanese title

English: The Mysterious New Guardian: Sailor Pluto Appears.

Japanese: Nazo no shin Senshi Sērā Purūtō tōjō (謎の新戦士セーラープルート登場)

Chibi-Usa falls into a coma after coming down with a mysterious fever. Usagi and the others are at a loss for what to do, when a Sailor Guardian calling herself Sailor Pluto suddenly appears before them.
name: The Secret of the Luna Sphere

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Magical Power of Darkness! Esmeraude's Invasion.

Japanee: Ankoku no maryoku! Esmerōdo no shinryaku (暗黒の魔力!エスメロードの侵略)

The Black Moon clan sends down its next operative, Esmeraude, to open the Dark Gate in 20th century Tokyo.
name: Emerald Takes Over

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Our Feelings are the Same! Usagi and Mamoru in Love Once Again.

Japanese: Omoi wa onaji! Usagi to Mamoru no ai futatabi (想いは同じ!うさぎと衛の愛再び)

Usagi is still depressed over Mamoru calling off their relationship. Ami and Mako try to cheer her up by taking Usagi to a promise ring workshop.
name: Promises Fulfilled

description:
Orignal English and Japanese title:

English: Venus Minako's Nurse Mayhem.

Japanese: Vīnasu Minako no nāsu daisōdō (ヴィーナス美奈子のナース大騒動)

A strange new flu is causing everyone in town to get sick, including the Sailor Guardians. Minako is the only one still healthy and takes it upon herself to look after her sick friends.
name: No Thanks, Nurse Venus

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Artemis's Adventure: the Monster Animal Kingdom.

Japanese: Arutemisu no bōken! Ma no dōbutsu ōkoku (アルテミスの冒険!魔の動物王国)

Artemis is out to prove he is capable after being teased by Luna. While on patrol, he encounters a suspicious-looking man who is gathering stray animals.
name: Dog Day For Artemis

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Terrifying Illusion! Ami All Alone.

Japanese: Kyōfu no gen'ei! Hitoribocchi no Ami (恐怖の幻影!ひとりぼっちの亜美)

The school test results are posted, and Ami is once again at the top of her class. But she soon finds herself becoming isolated after some of her schoolmates spread false rumors that she cheated on the test.
name: Smart Payoff

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Dark Gate Is Completed? the Targeted Elementary School.

Japanese: Ankoku gēto kansei? Nerawareta shōgakkō (暗黒ゲート完成?狙われた小学校)

After being out sick a couple of days, Chibi-Usa returns to school eager to see her friends. But to her surprise, her friends and teachers begin attacking her.
name: Child's Play

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Journey to the Future: Battle in the Space-Time Corridor.

Japanese: Mirai he no tabidachi! Jikū kairō no tatakai (未来への旅立ち!時空回廊の戦い)

Chibi-Usa finally decides to return to the future to save her mother. With support from the Sailor Guardians and Tuxedo Mask, she overcomes her fears and opens the Door of Space and Time.
name: Future Shocked

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Shocking Future: Demande's Dark Ambition.

Japanese: Shōgeki no mirai! Demando no kuroki yabō (衝撃の未来!デマンドの黒き野望)

Arriving in the future, the Sailor Guardians stand in shock as they see the ruins of what used to be Crystal Tokyo. Chibi-Usa goes missing afterwards, and as they search for her, the group encounters a man who looks exactly like Tuxedo Mask.
name: Legend Of The Negamoon

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Wiseman's Evil Hand! Chibiusa Disappears.

Japanese: Waizuman no mashu! Chibiusa shōmetsu (ワイズマンの魔手!ちびうさ消滅)

Tuxedo Mask rescues Sailor Moon from Black Moon’s castle. But before they can all celebrate, a giant dragon suddenly appears to destroy the Crystal Palace.
name: Jealousy's Just Reward

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Birth of Black Lady, The Queen of Darkness.

Japanese: Ankoku no joō Burakku Redi no tanjō (暗黒の女王ブラックレディの誕生)

Wiseman brainwashes Chibi-Usa and turns her into the Dark Queen known as Black Lady. Realizing that something has happened to Chibi-Usa, the Sailor Guardians return to present-day Earth to find her.
name: Birth of Wicked Lady

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Saphir Dies! Wiseman's Trap.

Japanese: Safīru zetsumei! Waizuman no wana (サフィール絶命!ワイズマンの罠)

Saphir learns of Wiseman’s true intentions and tries to warn his brother, only to be attacked by Wiseman himself. Barely managing to escape, Saphir is surprised when he is saved by Petz and her sisters.
name: Brotherly Love

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Believe in Love and the Future! Usagi's Determination.

Japanese: Ai to mirai wo shinjite! Usagi no kesshin (愛と未来を信じて!うさぎの決心)
name: Diamond In The Rough

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Final Battle Between Light and Darkness! Love Sworn to the Future.
